text: Aspergillus stercorarius is a species of fungus in the genus Aspergillus. It is from the Nidulantes section. The species was first described in 2016. It has been isolated from dung in Kerzaz, Sahara, and Kagh Islands. == References == stercorarius Category:Fungi described in 2016
title: Aspergillus stercorarius
